added.title: Jump City Rock
added.description: The Titans team up with Nandi and Thomas Bushell to take down The Joker.

added.title: Natural Gas
added.description: Outraged at the price they pay for water, gas, and electricity, the Titans go off the grid.

added.title: 50% Chad
added.description: Having grown tired of their current villains, the Titans hold an audition for a new arch nemesis.

added.title: The Score
added.description: The Titans have a hard time dealing with their emotions when an evil composer changes the music in their show.
Wanting their 365th episode to be extra special, the Titans head to the Warner Bros. studio lot to find a director.

added.title: The Singing
added.description: The town of Elmore becomes an all-singing, all-dancing mash up. Everyone has a song inside them, but do they really need to be heard?

added.title: The Deal
added.description: When Mom wins Employee of the Month at the Rainbow factory, Richard feels like he is never celebrated for all the work he does at home. Nicole is suspicious of how much he actually does, but when Richard goes on strike, his important role in keeping things under control becomes painfully clear...

added.title: The Puppets
added.description: While searching the attic for items to put in their yard sale, Gumball and Darwin stumble upon a load of their old toys. Darwin is especially pleased when he finds his old puppets, Frank and Howdy. However, as Darwin starts playing with them again, Gumball gradually realizes that Frank and Howdy are actually playing with Darwin...

added.title: The Line
added.description: The family has waited in line outside the movie theater all night. They are devastated when Larry tells them they won't get into the first screening of the Stellar Odyssey sequel. But, hardcore fans that they are, the Wattersons are determined to be the first to see the movie and so set about battling their way to the front of the queue.

added.title: The List
added.description: When the kids find out that Mom's life hasn't panned out exactly as she'd hoped, they try to make her day a bit easier by taking on her chores. However, they accidentally grab her bucket list instead of her to-do list and end up attempting to tick off all of Nicole's life goals.

added.title: Galactic Goodbyes
added.description: Craig and Sparkle Cadet put together a band to sing a goodbye to a long lost friend.

added.title: Craiggy & the Slime Factory
added.description: Craig and his friends get the first ever tour of the Slime Kids Slime Factory.

added.title: Bernard of the Creek Part 1
added.description: Craig is shocked when his older brother Bernard asks to join him at the Creek.

added.title: Bernard of the Creek Part 2
added.description: Bernard joins up with the wrong crowd of Creek Kids, forcing Craig to take action to save his brother.

added.title: Left in the Dark
added.description: Craig and his friends venture into an ancient cavern in their quest for the Heart of the Forest, and find something far more sinister.

added.title: Falafel's Car Keys
added.description: Apple & Onion are deemed responsible enough to borrow Falafel's car for their first road trip together. Nothing will go wrong, and they're going to make sure of that… by getting some practice in.

added.title: Truffle Season
added.description: It's Truffle Season, Apple and Onion are Truffle Hunters and they will stop at nothing to taste a truffle.

added.title: Lambporcini
added.description: Apple and Onion are very happy with their sweet new matching designer outfits they bought from known scam-artist Street Dog. That's until Chicken Nugget mistakes them for something they are not.

added.title: Open House Cookies
added.description: Jerk Chicken is selling his house and Apple and Onion have been showing a lot of interest which definitely has nothing to do with the delicious cookies out on offer.

added.title: Win It or Bin It
added.description: Apple and Onion are about to take ownership of a brand new luxury penthouse apartment and be rid of their roof shack for ever! All they need is a good reference from a previous landlord… Falafel.

added.title: Go Fish
added.description: While on a fishing trip, the Bears get attacked by a giant legendary fish.

added.title: Googs
added.description: The Bears win a tour of the infamous Googs corporate headquarters.

added.title: Paperboyz
added.description: The Baby Bears get jobs as paper boys.

added.title: Bear Squad
added.description: Tabes deputizes the Bears so they can go to the city and catch a thief.

added.title: Best Bears
added.description: The Bears must complete their Best-Man duties on the day of Darrell's wedding.

added.title: Abstract
added.description: As Jake goes through some personal changes, he's haunted by a sinister dream encounter with his brother Jermaine.

added.title: Ketchup
added.description: BMO and Marceline swap stories about their recent adventures.

added.title: Fionna and Cake and Fionna
added.description: An unexpected critic shows up at Ice King's latest Fionna and Cake book reading.

added.title: Whispers
added.description: While safeguarding a frightened Sweet P, Finn is led into a confrontation with an old foe.

added.title: Three Buckets
added.description: Finn and Fern's carefree visit to some old ruins turns disastrous.

added.title: Pops' Favorite Planet
added.description: When the guys have to sleep outside for the night, Pops wants to see his favorite planet.

added.title: Pam I Am
added.description: Benson has a crush on one of the Dome scientists, and he wants to sneak her a bucket of chicken wings so that he can ask her out.

added.title: Lame Lockdown
added.description: The head scientist puts Mordecai and Rigby on a 24-hour lockdown inside the Dome, but they want to sneak out and see one of their favorite bands.

added.title: VIP Members Only
added.description: Mordecai, Rigby, Muscle Man and High Five Ghost want to be VIP members at Cheeser's.

added.title: Deez Keys
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby need to make a deal with the scientists to get Benson's car keys back.

added.title: Find Your Bliss
added.description: When Bubbles blames a string of accidents on her imaginary friend Bliss, her sisters begin to think she's lost her mind.

added.title: Halt and Catch Silico
added.description: When a series of negative articles about the Powerpuff Girls are posted on the Internet, the girls track them back to Silico.

added.title: The Squashening
added.description: To escape a monster, the girls have to tell him a scary story.

added.title: Somewhere Over the Swingset
added.description: When the girls disobey the Professor and swing all the way over the swing set, they must deal with unexpected consequences.

added.title: People Pleaser
added.description: Blossom neglects her promise to Bubbles when she takes on too many things leaving Buttercup and Bubbles to fend for themselves.

added.title: Grown Up Stuff
added.description: Puppycorn doesn't want to grow up. To ease his woes, Unikitty spends the day teaching him all the fun things about being an adult.

added.title: Stop the Presses
added.description: Richard's newspapers aren't selling, so his friends pull out all the stops to put the printed word back on top.

added.title: Bedtime Stories
added.description: When Puppycorn can't fall asleep, Dr. Fox uses an invention to bring classic bedtime stories to life. But the gang's presence leads to some surprising twists in these popular tales.

added.title: Castles and Kitties
added.description: Score Creeper traps the gang in a fantasy role playing game where they must follow a complex set of rules to win their freedom.

added.title: Brain Trust
added.description: Dr. Fox accidentally transports the gang inside her brain, where they must control her movements to complete a dangerous experiment.

added.title: Clarence's Stormy Sleepover - Episode 1: The Phantom Clarence
added.description: Clarence is determined to throw the sleepover to end all sleepovers, his biggest party yet! Decorations, pillow fights, games. He's got it all. There's only one thing missing, guests! Clarence sets out to invite all his friends in town, but finds that they might need some convincing.

added.title: Clarence's Stormy Sleepover - Episode 2: Jeffrey Wendle
added.description: Mary and Chad are relieved to have a quiet day with Clarence's friend Jeff. Unlike Clarence, Jeff is polite, organized, and clean. However, they soon suspect there's something Jeff is hiding from them!

added.title: Clarence's Stormy Sleepover - Episode 3: Badgers N' Bunkers
added.description: As Sumo's dad Mel prepares the family for over-the-top doomsday scenarios, Sumo struggles to convince his family to let him keep a new pet.

added.title: Clarence's Stormy Sleepover - Episode 4: Dingus and McNobrain
added.description: Stuck in detention with Mr. Reese, an annoyed Belson is forced to go along with Mr. Reese's latest makeshift detective mystery.

added.title: Clarence's Stormy Sleepover - Episode 5: Bye Bye Baker
added.description: An ever-cheerful Clarence attempts to improvise a sleepover party with some of Aberdale's townsfolk in an unusual location - while everyone else panics.

added.title: RV Olympics
added.description: Pizza Steve and Mr. Gus compete in the RV Olympics.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Runs for President
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve run against one another in the RV presidential race.

added.title: Face Fix
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve help Mr. Gus try to get his face back to normal before an important photo shoot.

added.title: The Phone Call
added.description: A threatening phone call from a stranger causes the gang to panic.

added.title: Uncle Cupid
added.description: Cupid, too lonely to perform his Valentine's Day duties, comes to Uncle Grandpa for help.
